It looks like you want a project plan for a Leftover Food Management System as a web application. Here's a structured approach to building this project:

Project Plan: Leftover Food Management System (Web Application)
1. Introduction
A web-based Leftover Food Management System that helps restaurants, hotels, and individuals donate surplus food to NGOs or food banks efficiently.

2. Features
User Roles
Donors (Restaurants, Hotels, Individuals)
Receivers (NGOs, Food Banks)
Admin (Manages users and operations)
Core Features
âœ… User Authentication (Signup/Login for donors, receivers, and admin)
âœ… Food Donation Form (Donors can post surplus food details with location & expiration time)
âœ… Food Request System (NGOs can request available food items)
âœ… Real-Time Notifications (Donors get notified when an NGO requests food)
âœ… Location-Based Matching (Connect donors with nearby receivers)
âœ… Dashboard & Reports (Admin can track donations and impact metrics)
âœ… Google Maps API Integration (For location tracking and directions)

3. Tech Stack
Layer	Technologies
Frontend	React.js, TailwindCSS
Backend	Node.js, Express.js
Database	MongoDB / Firebase
Authentication	Firebase Auth / JWT
Cloud Storage	AWS S3 / Firebase Storage
Payment (Optional for Donations)	Stripe / Razorpay
Deployment	Vercel (Frontend) + AWS/GCP (Backend)
